-- Japanese Sold Net 398.2 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week
-- B y   M i n h   B u i
-- 2013-01-09T23:53:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-09/japanese-sold-net-398-2-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
sellers of foreign bonds during the week ended Jan. 4 according
to figures based on reports from designated major investors
released by the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors sold 398.2 billion yen ($4.5 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, bought 6.8 billion yen in overseas stocks
and bought 21.2 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net sale of 370.2 billion yen.  Foreign investors sold 1.8 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
bought 178.9 billion yen in stocks, and bought 458.1 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net purchase of 635.2
billion yen.    To contact the reporter on this story:
